FBIS3-30892 "dreeu028aa_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-028 Document Type:Daily Report 10 February 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Karadzic `Only' Prepared To Discuss Massacre AU0902204494 Paris AFP in English 2021 GMT 9 Feb 94 AU0902204494 Paris AFP Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Geneva, Feb 9 (AFP) -- Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic arrived here Wednesday [9 February] for talks with the other two warring parties, amid a growing threat of NATO air strikes against his faction. Karadzic was enigmatic as he arrived here, declining all comment other than saying "I am only prepared to talk about the massacre in Sarajevo" which killed 68 people on Saturday [5 February]. The new round of talks due Thursday [10 February] has been scheduled for weeks, well before the massacre in a Sarajevo market place which has sparked intense international pressure for air strikes. [passage omitted]
